A 70-year-old woman, Mrs Sidikak jimoh suspected to have been killed for ritual purposes was on Monday found dead at her Ayetoro residence in Ogbagi Akoko, Akoko Northwest Local Government Area of Ondo state. The lifeless body of the grandmother was found in her own pool of blood at the early hours of today. It was gathered that her assailants had removed many parts of her body and wanted to set the dead body ablaze. A source told LEADERSHIP that some of the removed parts of her body was forgotten by her assailants before leaving the scene. Efforts to speak with the paramount ruler of Ogbagi the Owa of Ogbagi Oba Ade Olasehinde proved abortive. Both the police Area Commander for Ikare Assistant Commissioner of police, Razak Rauf, and the Divisional Police Officer for Ogbagi Kunle Fabuluje, confirmed the incident. They said full scale investigation has commenced while the corpse has been deposited at State Specialist hospital Ikare mortuary. 